,Recommended,274480,18470490,"Posted: 14 October, 2015",all,The Mi-Go 13,"TL:DR - If you love ARPGs and want to play a very unique interpretation of the genre, buy this game. It is wonderful.Drox Operative is a highly unique experience which is a rare feat in today's world of games that are immediately familiar and easily described as ""Game A"" combined with ""Game B"". Although not flashy, it has heart, creativity, fun, reward, and innovation in spades. The play is direct and simple as is typical for ARPGs but very deep and customizable, and the choices of what equipment to keep and what to trade away goes well beyond simply choosing which bauble has the biggest numbers on it. The best adjective I can use for this game is 'rewarding'. The experience of playing Drox Operative FAR FAR outstrips the moderate price tag that Texas-based Soldak Entertainment is asking for it.Drox Operative is a true hidden gem that combines 4x space, ARPG, and resource management into a game that is simple to play, hard to master and always evolving because of the choices you make. All of this combines to make a game that feels alive and dangerous in a way that other ARPGs just don't have. It is an unexpected treasure nestled in a hidden corner of a genre that has many fine offerings. The only disappointing thing about this game is that so few people know about it. With wider coverage this game would be legendary.If you love ARPGs but want something that takes the genre to the next level, play the free demo. Better still, save yourself some time and just buy the game. The galaxy awaits.Happy gaming,M13"
