,Recommended,274480,9247122,"Posted: 24 February, 2014",all,generalzee,"In short: Space Diablo.In more detail, Drox Operative is like the ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ child result of a one night stand between Galactic Civilizations and Diablo. You have some interesting diplomacy options that allow you to protect yourself and the ability to sell stolen technologies tied in with a point-and-click, top-down, action-rpg. The mechanics are simple enough to learn, and ship configuration is a series of tough choices adding some good depth.Downsides of this game are that loot optimization is basically all you're doing, though it is very satisfying. Leveling starts slowing around level 15 and pacing in general can be quite slow at times (Especially when trying to convince 2 of your allies to ally themselves so you can win).Overall, the game is addicting and, most importantly, fun. If you like Diablo-style games, this is highly recommended. Less recommended to those seeking a Gal-Civ like game."
